                    <div class="info-box">
                        <strong>What is Self-Explanation?</strong><br>
                        Self-explanation is when you actively think about and articulate what new information means to you, connecting it to what you already know. Research shows this dramatically improves learning and retention.
                    </div>

                    <h3>How This Works:</h3>
                    <p>You'll read short passages about the renal system, then pause to explain the information in your own words. This helps you:</p>
                    <ul style="margin-left: 30px; margin-top: 15px; line-height: 2;">
                        <li>Process information more deeply</li>
                        <li>Identify gaps in your understanding</li>
                        <li>Connect new knowledge to existing knowledge</li>
                        <li>Remember information longer</li>
